41 // __cpp_exceptions is referred from
42 // https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/libstdc++/manual/using_exceptions.html
43 // gcc < 5 does not define __cpp_exceptions but __EXCEPTIONS,
44 // Microsoft C++ Compiler does not provide an option to disable exceptions
45 #ifndef DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
46 #if __cpp_exceptions || __EXCEPTIONS \
47  || (defined(_MSC_VER) && !defined(__clang__))
48 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 1
49 #else
50 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 0
51 #endif
52 #endif
53 
54 #if defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)
55 #define DNNL_TRAP() __builtin_trap()
56 #elif defined(__INTEL_COMPILER) || defined(_MSC_VER)
57 #define DNNL_TRAP() __debugbreak()
58 #else
59 #error "unknown compiler"
60 #endif
61 
62 #if DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
63 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) throw error(status, msg)
64 #else
65 #include <cstdio>
66 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) \
67  do { \
68  fputs(msg, stderr); \
69  DNNL_TRAP(); \
70  } while (0)
71 #endif

87 struct error : public std::exception {
88  dnnl_status_t status;
89  const char *message;
90 
95  error(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message)
96  : status(status), message(message) {}
97 
99  const char *what() const noexcept override { return message; }
100 
106  static void wrap_c_api(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message) {
107  if (status != dnnl_success) DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, message);
108  }
109 };
110 
112 template <typename T>
113 struct handle_traits {};
114 
128 template <typename T, typename traits = handle_traits<T>>
129 struct handle {
130 private:
131  static dnnl_status_t dummy_destructor(T) { return dnnl_success; }
132  std::shared_ptr<typename std::remove_pointer<T>::type> data_ {0};
133 
134 protected:
135  bool operator==(const T other) const { return other == data_.get(); }
136  bool operator!=(const T other) const { return !(*this == other); }
137 
138 public:
146  handle() = default;
147 
149  handle(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
151  handle<T, traits> &operator=(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
153  handle(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
155  handle<T, traits> &operator=(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
156 
162  explicit handle(T t, bool weak = false) { reset(t, weak); }
163 
169  void reset(T t, bool weak = false) {
170  data_.reset(t, weak ? &dummy_destructor : traits::destructor);
171  }
172 
178  T get(bool allow_empty = false) const {
179  T result = data_.get();
180  if (allow_empty == false && result == nullptr)
181  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(
182  dnnl_invalid_arguments, "object is not initialized");
183  return result;
184  }
185 
190  explicit operator T() const { return get(true); }
191 
195  explicit operator bool() const { return get(true) != nullptr; }
196 
203  bool operator==(const handle<T, traits> &other) const {
204  return other.data_.get() == data_.get();
205  }
206 
213  bool operator!=(const handle &other) const { return !(*this == other); }
214 };

360 dnnl::primitive::kind primitive::get_kind() const {
361  const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = get_primitive_desc();
362  // TODO (Roma): the code below is only needed because get_primitive_desc
363  // returns a C type.
364  dnnl_primitive_kind_t kind;
365  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
366  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&kind),
367  "could not get a primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
368  return static_cast<dnnl::primitive::kind>(kind);
369 }

613 #define DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(enum_name) \
614  inline enum_name operator|(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
615  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
616  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
617  } \
618 \
619  inline enum_name operator&(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
620  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
621  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
622  } \
623 \
624  inline enum_name operator^(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
625  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
626  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
627  } \
628 \
629  inline enum_name &operator|=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
630  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
631  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
632  return lhs; \
633  } \
634 \
635  inline enum_name &operator&=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
636  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
637  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
638  return lhs; \
639  } \
640 \
641  inline enum_name &operator^=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
642  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
643  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
644  return lhs; \
645  } \
646 \
647  inline enum_name operator~(enum_name rhs) { \
648  return static_cast<enum_name>(~static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
649  }
650 
651 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(normalization_flags)
652 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(rnn_flags)

964  void get_output_scales(int &mask, std::vector<float> &scales) const {
965  dnnl_dim_t count;
966  int c_mask;
967  const float *c_scales;
968  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_get_output_scales(
969  get(), &count, &c_mask, &c_scales),
970  "could not get primitive output scales attribute");
971  scales.resize(count);
972 
973  mask = c_mask;
974  for (dnnl_dim_t c = 0; c < count; ++c)
975  scales[c] = c_scales[c];
976  }
977

1022  (dnnl_dim_t)scales.size(), mask, &scales[0]),
1023  "could not set primitive output scales attribute");
1024  }

1218 
1221  engine() = default;
1222 
1227  static size_t get_count(kind kind) {
1228  return dnnl_engine_get_count(convert_to_c(kind));
1229  }
1230 
1236  engine(kind kind, size_t index) {
1237  dnnl_engine_t engine;
1238  error::wrap_c_api(
1239  dnnl_engine_create(&engine, convert_to_c(kind), index),
1240  "could not create an engine");
1241  reset(engine);
1242  }
1243 
1244 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
1245  engine(kind kind, cl_device_id device, cl_context context) {
1252  dnnl_engine_t engine;
1253  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_create_ocl(
1254  &engine, convert_to_c(kind), device, context),
1255  "could not create an engine");
1256  reset(engine);
1257  }
1258 #endif
1259 
1264  engine(const handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_t> &pd) {
1265  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
1266  error::wrap_c_api(
1267  dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
1268  dnnl::convert_to_c(dnnl::query::engine), 0, &c_engine),
1269  "could not get an engine from a primitive_desc");
1270  reset(c_engine, true);
1271  }
1272 
1275  kind get_kind() const {
1276  dnnl_engine_kind_t kind;
1277  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_kind(get(), &kind),
1278  "could not get kind of an engine");
1279  return static_cast<engine::kind>(kind);
1280  }
1281 
1282 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
1283  cl_context get_ocl_context() const {
1286  cl_context context = nullptr;
1287  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_context(get(), &context),
1288  "could not get an OpenCL context fron an engine");
1289  return context;
1290  }
1291 
1294  cl_device_id get_ocl_device() const {
1295  cl_device_id device = nullptr;
1296  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_device(get(), &device),
1297  "could not get an OpenCL device fron an engine");
1298  return device;
1299  }
1300 #endif
1301 
1307  template <class primitive_desc>
1308  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd) {
1309  return query(pd, dnnl::query::engine);
1310  }
1311 
1312 private:
1313  static dnnl_engine_kind_t convert_to_c(kind kind) {
1314  return static_cast<dnnl_engine_kind_t>(kind);
1315  }
1316 
1317  template <class primitive_desc>
1318  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd, dnnl::query what) {
1319  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
1320  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
1321  dnnl::convert_to_c(what), 0, &c_engine),
1322  "could not get an engine from a primitive_desc");
1323  return engine(c_engine, true);
1324  }
1325 };

1338 template <>
1339 struct handle_traits<dnnl_stream_t> {
1340  static constexpr auto destructor = &dnnl_stream_destroy;
1341 };
1343 
1345 struct stream : public handle<dnnl_stream_t> {
1346  using handle::handle;
1347 
1349  enum class flags : unsigned {
1352  default_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1354  in_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1356  out_of_order = dnnl_stream_out_of_order,
1358  default_flags = dnnl_stream_default_flags,
1359  };
1360 
1363  stream() = default;
1364 
1370  stream(const engine &engine, flags flags = flags::default_flags) {
1371  dnnl_stream_t stream;
1372  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create(&stream, engine.get(),
1373  static_cast<dnnl_stream_flags_t>(flags)),
1374  "could not create a stream");
1375  reset(stream);
1376  }
1377 
1378 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
1379  stream(const engine &engine, cl_command_queue queue) {
1384  dnnl_stream_t stream;
1385  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create_ocl(&stream, engine.get(), queue),
1386  "could not create a stream");
1387  reset(stream);
1388  }
1389 
1392  cl_command_queue get_ocl_command_queue() const {
1393  cl_command_queue queue = nullptr;
1394  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_get_ocl_command_queue(get(), &queue),
1395  "could not get an OpenCL command queue from a stream");
1396  return queue;
1397  }
1398 #endif
1399 
1402  stream &wait() {
1403  error::wrap_c_api(
1404  dnnl_stream_wait(get()), "could not wait on a stream");
1405  return *this;
1406  }
1407 };

2013  desc(const memory::dims &dims, data_type data_type,
2014  format_tag format_tag) {

2018  dims.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &dims[0],
2019  convert_to_c(data_type), convert_to_c(format_tag)),
2020  "could not construct a memory descriptor using a format "
2021  "tag");
2022  }

2040  dims.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &dims[0],
2041  convert_to_c(data_type),
2042  strides.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &strides[0]),

2310  memory::dim query_s64(query what) const {
2311  memory::dim res;
2312  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
2313  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(what), 0, &res);
2314  return status == dnnl_success ? res : 0;
2315  }
2316 
2331  memory::desc query_md(query what, int idx = 0) const {
2332  std::vector<query> valid_q {query::src_md, query::diff_src_md,
2333  query::weights_md, query::diff_weights_md, query::dst_md,
2334  query::diff_dst_md, query::workspace_md, query::scratchpad_md,
2335  query::exec_arg_md};
2336  if (!std::any_of(valid_q.cbegin(), valid_q.cend(),
2337  [=](query q) { return what == q; }))
2338  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2339  "memory descriptor query is invalid");
2340 
2341  const dnnl_memory_desc_t *cdesc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query_md(
2342  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(what), idx);
2343  return cdesc ? memory::desc(*cdesc) : memory::desc();
2344  }

2352  return query_md(query::src_md, idx);
2353  }

2380  }

2495  dnnl_primitive_desc_t new_pd;

2500 
2514  primitive_desc_base(
2515  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd, dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind)
2516  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind::undef) {}
2517 
2529  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
2530  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind)
2531  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, prop_kind, prop_kind) {}
2532 
2546  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
2547  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1,
2548  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2) {
2549  // It is OK to pass an empty primitive descriptor
2550  if (pd == nullptr) return;
2551 
2552  dnnl_status_t rc;
2553 
2554  dnnl_primitive_kind_t c_prim_kind = convert_to_c(prim_kind);
2555  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
2556  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
2557 
2558  // Check that primitive kind matches
2559  dnnl_primitive_kind_t pd_kind;
2560  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
2561  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_kind);
2562  error::wrap_c_api(
2563  rc, "could not get primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
2564  if (pd_kind != c_prim_kind)
2565  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2566  "primitive descriptor operation kind mismatch");
2567 
2568  // Check that propagation kind matches
2569  dnnl_prop_kind_t pd_prop_kind;
2570  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
2571  pd, dnnl_query_prop_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_prop_kind);
2572 
2573  // Something went wrong
2574  if (rc != dnnl_success && rc != dnnl_unimplemented)
2575  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2576  "could not get propagation kind from the primitive "
2577  "descriptor");
2578 
2579  // Everything is fine
2580  if ((rc == dnnl_unimplemented && c_prop_kind1 == dnnl_prop_kind_undef)
2581  || (rc == dnnl_success
2582  && (pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
2583  || pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind2))) {
2584  reset_with_clone(pd);
2585  return;
2586  }
2587 
2588  // We could get the propagation kind but there is a mismatch
2589  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2590  "primitive descriptor propagation kind mismatch");
2591  }
2592 
2593 protected:
2594  using base = primitive_desc_base;
2595 };
2596

2734 inline std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> convert_to_c(
2735  const std::vector<memory::desc> &mems) {
2736  std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> c_mems;
2737  c_mems.reserve(mems.size());

2740  return c_mems;

2953 
2976  primitive_desc(const_dnnl_op_desc_t desc, const primitive_attr *attr,
2977  const engine &engine, const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t hint_fwd_pd,
2978  bool allow_empty = false)
2979  : allow_empty_(allow_empty) {
2980  dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t iterator = nullptr;
2981  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_create(&iterator,
2982  desc, attr ? attr->get() : nullptr, engine.get(), hint_fwd_pd);
2983  if (!allow_empty)
2984  error::wrap_c_api(
2985  status, "could not create a primitive descriptor iterator");
2986  pd_iterator.reset(iterator);
2987  fetch_impl();
2988  }
2989 
2994  bool next_impl() {
2995  dnnl_status_t status
2996  = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_next(pd_iterator.get());
2997  if (status == dnnl_iterator_ends) return false;
2998  error::wrap_c_api(
2999  status, "could not advance a primitive descriptor iterator");
3000  fetch_impl();
3001  return true;
3002  }
3003 
3004 private:
3005  bool allow_empty_ = false;
3006  handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t> pd_iterator;
3007  void fetch_impl() {
3008  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_fetch(
3009  pd_iterator.get(allow_empty_));
3010  error::wrap_c_api(pd != nullptr || allow_empty_ ? dnnl_success
3011  : dnnl_runtime_error,
3012  "could not fetch a primitive descriptor from a primitive "
3013  "descriptor iterator");
3014  reset(pd);
3015  }
3016 };

6821  inner_product_backward_weights(const primitive_desc &pd) : primitive(pd) {}
6822 };

6835 struct rnn_primitive_desc_base : public primitive_desc {
6836  using primitive_desc::primitive_desc;
6837 
6839  rnn_primitive_desc_base() = default;
6840 
6848  rnn_primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind,
6849  dnnl::algorithm cell_kind)
6850  : rnn_primitive_desc_base(pd, prop_kind, prop_kind, cell_kind) {}
6851 
6854  memory::desc src_layer_desc() const { return base::src_desc(0); }
6855 
6860  memory::desc src_iter_desc() const { return base::src_desc(1); }
6861 
6864  memory::desc src_iter_c_desc() const { return base::src_desc(2); }
6865 
6868  memory::desc weights_layer_desc() const { return base::weights_desc(0); }
6869 
6872  memory::desc weights_iter_desc() const { return base::weights_desc(1); }
6873 
6878  memory::desc bias_desc() const { return base::weights_desc(2); }
6879 
6882  memory::desc dst_layer_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(0); }
6883 
6888  memory::desc dst_iter_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(1); }
6889 
6892  memory::desc dst_iter_c_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(2); }
6893 
6896  memory::desc diff_src_layer_desc() const { return base::diff_src_desc(0); }
6897 
6902  memory::desc diff_src_iter_desc() const { return base::diff_src_desc(1); }
6903 
6906  memory::desc diff_src_iter_c_desc() const { return base::diff_src_desc(2); }
6907 
6910  memory::desc diff_weights_layer_desc() const {
6911  return base::diff_weights_desc(0);
6912  }
6913 
6916  memory::desc diff_weights_iter_desc() const {
6917  return base::diff_weights_desc(1);
6918  }
6919 
6924  memory::desc diff_bias_desc() const { return base::diff_weights_desc(2); }
6925 
6928  memory::desc diff_dst_layer_desc() const { return base::diff_dst_desc(0); }
6929 
6934  memory::desc diff_dst_iter_desc() const { return base::diff_dst_desc(1); }
6935 
6938  memory::desc diff_dst_iter_c_desc() const { return base::diff_dst_desc(2); }
6939 
6940 protected:
6941  using rnn_base = rnn_primitive_desc_base;
6942 
6943  // (Deliberately not using doxygen comments)
6944  //
6945  // Constructs an RNN primitive descriptor base from a C API primitive
6946  // descriptor while checking that it actually describes the expected
6947  // primitive by comparing propagation and primitive kinds. Caller can
6948  // pass two options propagation kinds. This is typically used to check
6949  // that propagation kind is inference or training forward propagation.
6950  //
6951  // @param pd C API primitive descriptor.
6952  // @param prop_kind1 Expected propagation kind.
6953  // @param prop_kind2 Expected propagation kind.
6954  // @param cell_kind Expected cell kind.
6955  rnn_primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
6956  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2,
6957  dnnl::algorithm cell_kind) {
6958  dnnl_rnn_desc_t *rnn_d;
6959  dnnl_status_t rc;
6960  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd, dnnl_query_rnn_d, 0, &rnn_d);
6961  error::wrap_c_api(rc,
6962  "could not retrieve a descriptor from a primitive descriptor "
6963  "for an RNN primitive");
6964 
6965  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
6966  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
6967  dnnl_alg_kind_t c_cell_kind = convert_to_c(cell_kind);
6968 
6969  bool ok = rnn_d->primitive_kind == dnnl_rnn
6970  && (rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
6971  || rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind2)
6972  && rnn_d->cell_kind == c_cell_kind;
6973 
6974  if (!ok)
6975  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
6976  "mismatch between expected and provided descriptors for an "
6977  "RNN primitive");
6978 
6979  reset_with_clone(pd);
6980  }
6981 };

9279  const memory::desc &diff_dst_desc) {
9280  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_backward_desc_init(&data,
9281  convert_to_c(algorithm), &factors[0],
9282  &diff_src_desc.data, &diff_dst_desc.data),
9283  "could not create a resampling backward data descriptor");
9284  }
9285  };

9306  bool allow_empty = false)

9308  hint_fwd_pd.get(), allow_empty) {}

9326  bool allow_empty = false)

9328  allow_empty) {}

9338  dnnl::prop_kind::backward_data) {}

9452 inline primitive::primitive(const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t c_pd) {
9453  dnnl_primitive_t result;
9454  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_create(&result, c_pd),
9455  "could not create a primitive");
9456  reset(result);
9457 }
9458 
9459 inline primitive::primitive(const primitive_desc &pd) : primitive(pd.get()) {}
9460 
9461 inline void primitive::execute(
9462  stream &stream, const std::unordered_map<int, memory> &args) const {
9463  std::vector<dnnl_exec_arg_t> c_args;
9464  c_args.reserve(args.size());
9465  for (const auto &a : args)
9466  c_args.push_back({a.first, a.second.get(true)});
9467 
9468  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_execute(get(), stream.get(),
9469  (int)c_args.size(), c_args.data()),
9470  "could not execute a primitive");
9471 }
